            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Why another? Why special?\r\n\r\n`vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview` doc say:\r\n\r\n> {opts} (table) with optional fields (additional keys are passed on to [nvim_open_win() (https://neovim.io/doc/user/api.html#nvim_open_win()))\r\n\r\n`vim.api.nvim_open_win` doc say:\r\n\r\n> noautocmd: If true then no buffer-related autocommand events such as [BufEnter](https://neovim.io/doc/user/autocmd.html#BufEnter), [BufLeave](https://neovim.io/doc/user/autocmd.html#BufLeave) or [BufWinEnter](https://neovim.io/doc/user/autocmd.html#BufWinEnter) may fire from calling this function.\r\n\r\nSo this is the standard option.\r\n\r\n> Need a clear, concise use-case with sample code. Linking to external issues isn't sufficient.\r\n\r\nAuto buffer save / code fmt on BufferLeave, vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview on hover.\r\n",
